excerpt: Ushuaia is a resort town in Argentina. It's located on the Tierra del Fuego archipelago, the southernmost tip of South America, nicknamed the “End of the World.” The windswept town, perched on a steep hill, is surrounded by the Martial Mountains and the Beagle Channel. It's the gateway to Antarctica cruises and tours to nearby Isla Yécapasela, known as “Penguin Island” for its penguin colonies.
detail_description: Ushuaia, a resort town in Argentina, is situated on the Tierra del Fuego archipelago at the southernmost tip of South America. Known as the 'End of the World,' this windswept town is surrounded by the Martial Mountains and the Beagle Channel. It serves as a starting point for Antarctica cruises and tours to nearby Isla Yécapasela, also called 'Penguin Island' due to its penguin colonies.
name: Ushuaia
address: V9410, Tierra del Fuego Province, Argentina

detail_description: HeliUshuaia, a local helicopter tour operator in Ushuaia, provides various flight options for visitors. These include a 7-minute flight over Ushuaia and the Beagle Channel, a 15-minute journey extending to Laguna Esmeralda, and an extended 30-minute excursion into the Andes Mountains with a landing and champagne celebration.
name: C. Laguna Esmeralda
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: Museum of local history & natural history, with exhibits on sailing, whaling, seabirds & more.
detail_description: Museo del Fin del Mundo, also called the End of the World Museum, is a local history and natural history museum that features displays on sailing, whaling, seabirds, early penal colonies and native life. The museum was established in 1903 within a former bank building.
name: Museo del Fin del Mundo
address: Av. Maipú 173, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: 19th-century prison building housing maritime, Antarctic, jail & marine museums.
detail_description: The Museo Marítimo y del Presidio de Ushuaia is a historic 19th-century prison building that now houses multiple museums. Located on the grounds of Ushuaia's naval base, it features the Maritime Museum, which showcases indigenous canoe-making skills, navigational history of Tierra del Fuego and Cape Horn, Antarctic exploration, and even displays on famous jails worldwide.
name: Museo Marítimo y del Presidio de Ushuaia
address: Gobernador Paz y Yaganes Ex Presidio, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Glaciar Martial Ushuaia is a must-visit destination just outside the city, offering a range of activities for nature enthusiasts. The area features a stunning lake perfect for fishing and hiking, with hills that provide scenic views and adventure opportunities. A short distance away, visitors can take a ski lift to reach the glacier, which sits 1,050 meters above sea level and serves as an important water source for Ushuaia.
name: Glaciar Martial Ushuaia
address: Yowen, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Kaupé Restaurant is a family-owned high-end establishment offering delicious Argentine cuisine with beautiful harbor views. The restaurant is known for its seafood dishes such as king crab, black hake, and fresh oysters prepared with a contemporary twist. It prides itself on using the freshest local ingredients and offers an impressive selection of Argentine wines. While it may be relatively expensive, the food is considered worth the price by many patrons.
name: Kaupé Restaurant
address: Pres. Julio Argentino Roca 470, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: El Viejo Marino is a popular seafood restaurant in Ushuaia known for its delicious king crab dishes. It's recommended to arrive early as there is often a line forming before the doors open at 7pm. Despite being slightly cheaper than other crab restaurants in town, it offers fresh and tasty options that are well worth the wait. The star dish at El Viejo Marino is the spider crab, and many locals flock to this spot due to its great prices and quality seafood.
name: El Viejo Marino
address: Av. Maipú 227, V9410BJE Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Tante Sara - Café & Bar is a long-standing establishment in Ushuaia, known for its classic signature dishes that combine the best pasta with fresh seafood from the Beagle Channel. The restaurant offers a cozy atmosphere and serves dishes throughout the day, from breakfast to dinner. Their menu features standout items like crab raviolins, black sea fruit spaghetti, and a bacon-wrapped trout dish. Tante Sara is also renowned for its pastry and confectionery offerings.
name: Tante Sara - Café & Bar
address: V9410BFB, BFH, Av. San Martín 701, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Ramos Generales El Almacén is a charming café located on the waterfront, reminiscent of an old frontier general store. The atmosphere is filled with relics and antiques, including a hand-cranked Victrola phonograph. The menu offers a variety of options, from fresh-baked bread to scrumptious lemon croissants. Visitors can enjoy submarino, a mug of hot milk with a bar of dark chocolate, perfect alongside a panini.
name: Ramos Generales El Almacén
address: Av. Maipú 749, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: The "End of the World Sign" is a popular tourist attraction in Ushuaia, offering visitors a unique experience on a replica of a steam-driven "prison train" through Tierra del Fuego National Park. The area was once a prison town where criminals endured harsh conditions, and the tour provides insight into their transportation and life in reconstructed camps.
name: End of the World Sign
address: Maupu, Pres. Julio Argentino Roca y, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Paso Garibaldi is a must-visit spot in the Ushuaia area. The breathtaking views of Lago Escondido from the top are truly awe-inspiring, with snow-capped peaks and pristine landscapes. As you descend through the old roads, you'll be immersed in nature at its best.
name: Paso Garibaldi
address: Gdor. Deloqui 133, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: María Lola Restó is a popular dining spot in Ushuaia, offering a modern and diverse menu inspired by Argentine and Patagonian cuisine. The restaurant specializes in seafood dishes, with the Fuegian trout risotto being a standout option. Situated in the heart of Ushuaia, María Lola provides breathtaking views, making it an ideal choice for couples seeking a special dining experience.
name: María Lola Restó
address: Gdor. Deloqui 1048, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: La Cantina Fueguina De Freddy is a delightful seafood and Argentine cuisine restaurant nestled in the heart of Ushuaia, Argentina. Renowned for its exceptional service, particularly from the friendly waiter Jorge, this eatery offers an array of standout dishes that are sure to tantalize your taste buds. Guests rave about the hot king crab, the unique 'paella del fin del mundo,' and delectable options like grilled trout stuffed with cheese and bacon or gratin scallops.
name: La Cantina Fueguina De Freddy
address: Av. San Martín 300-398, V9410BFQ Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Dublin is a popular Irish pub in Ushuaia that is always busy. It serves standard bar food, including appetizers, sandwiches, burgers and pizza, as well as locally produced Beagle beer.
name: Dublin
address: 9 de Julio 168, V9410DDD Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: The Flea Market Feria de Artesanos is a popular event in Mexico City where artisanal vendors sell their handmade goods. It's a great place to find unique souvenirs, and you can often find bargains on items like clothing, jewelry, and pottery.
name: Feria de Artesanos
address: 99,, Comodoro Augusto Laserre Sur 1, Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Martial Glacier, located just a few kilometers above the center of Ushuaia, offers nature lovers a chance to admire stunning views of the city, Beagle Channel, and the glacier itself. Outdoor enthusiasts can engage in activities like trekking, horse riding, mountain biking, and sport fishing. The area also features unexplored sites for excursions. Additionally, visitors can explore the Centro Invernal Cerro Castor ski resort nearby for optimal snow conditions from May to October.
name: Martial Glacier
address: Arturo Coronado 486, Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Av. San Martín is a bustling main avenue where you can leisurely stroll and take your pick from various dining options, souvenir shops, and cozy cafes for a delightful evening. As you wander towards the waterfront, you'll be greeted by the sight of imposing cargo ships, elegant cruise liners, and lively fishing boats unloading their fresh catches. Don't miss the chance to visit one of the numerous craft beer bars to savor a pint of locally brewed beer!
name: Av. San Martín
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Bahia Encerrada is a picturesque body of water located in Ushuaia, offering various activities throughout the year. In winter, it freezes over and becomes an ice skating rink, while in summer, visitors can cross it via a catwalk to reach the peninsula on the other side. The surrounding area features scenic walking and running paths such as the 0.5 km Paseo de los Antiguos Pobladores park and a 2 km loop around the lake.
name: Bahia Encerrada
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego Province, Argentina

excerpt: Range with a popular hiking trail to the summit of Martial Glacier, offering panoramas of Ushuaia.
detail_description: Martial Mountains, located near Ushuaia, Argentina, offer a popular hiking trail to the summit of Martial Glacier with stunning panoramas of the city. The area is also known for challenging activities like cross-country skiing at Cerro Castor and dog-sledding excursions. Ushuaia itself is a vibrant city surrounded by the Martial mountains, Parque Nacional Tierra del Fuego, and the Beagle Channel.
name: Martial Mountains
address: Tierra del Fuego Province, Argentina

excerpt: Down-to-earth hostel featuring a garden, a terrace & a TV lounge, plus a communal kitchen.
detail_description: Oshovia Hostel is a charming accommodation located in Ushuaia, just a short distance from Encerrada Bay. This down-to-earth hostel offers non-smoking rooms, free WiFi, and a shared lounge for guests to enjoy. The property has a tour desk and is conveniently situated near popular attractions such as Tierra del Fuego National Park and Yamana Museum.
name: Oshovia Hostel
address: GYA, Primer Argentino 127, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Martial Glacier Skiing, located near Ushuaia, offers breathtaking views of the Beagle Channel. The glacier is accessible by a long hike or an inexpensive taxi ride followed by a walk or chairlift ascent. During winter, it provides the closest skiing opportunity to Ushuaia. Visitors can also explore Laguna Esmerelda and enjoy skiing at the nearby Cerro Castor Ski Resort. The hike to Martial Glacier varies in difficulty, with options for different skill levels.
name: Glaciar Martial Pista de Esquí
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: El Mercado Ushuaia is a great spot for nourishing food before or after trekking, offering a variety of breakfasts, lunches, sandwiches, and desserts. The menu includes an amazing variety of beers and cocktails. While the service could be more attentive at times, the food is truly delicious with huge portions for the price. The restaurant also offers a selection of pastas, salads, stews, cheeses, meats in the deli section as well as tempting pastries.
name: El Mercado Ushuaia
address: Av. San Martín 1488, V9410BGO Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Kalma Resto is a renowned restaurant located in Ushuaia, offering a perfect blend of exquisite cuisine and breathtaking panoramic views. Led by chef Jorge Monopoli, the menu features an array of options including fresh seafood, grilled meats, and vegetarian dishes that showcase the authentic flavors of Southern Patagonia.
name: Kalma Resto
address: Gdor. Manuel Fernández Valdez 293, V9410IEB Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Volver is a classic restaurant in Ushuaia that stands out for its charming ambiance and historical feel. Housed in a wooden building resembling a historical museum, it offers a warm and familiar atmosphere. The owner and chef, Lino Gomez Adillon, is an expert in traditional Fuegian cuisine and enjoys sharing meals with visitors. The restaurant's specialty is the centolla, served in various cooking styles and paired with different sauces.
name: Volver
address: Av. Maipú 37, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Taberna Del Viejo Lobo is a unique tavern located above the Ushuaia thematic gallery, offering a great spot for an aperitif or light meal with a fantastic view of the Beagle Channel. The tavern also houses a thematic gallery featuring dioramas. While the gallery is currently closed for renovation, the gastronomy experience remains open and impressive. Despite its unassuming appearance, this southernmost tavern surprises visitors with its amazing food and quick service.
name: Taberna Del Viejo Lobo
address: Av. San Martín 160, V9410BFO Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: HeliUshuaia offers an unforgettable experience with its helicopter tours over Ushuaia and the surrounding mountains. The professional staff and experienced pilots ensure a safe and enjoyable journey, even in potentially cloudy or foggy conditions. Passengers can opt for a 30-45 minute flight, which may include a landing by a picturesque mountain lake where champagne is served. The breathtaking views from the helicopter provide an unparalleled perspective of the stunning landscapes at 'the end of the world.'
name: HeliUshuaia
address: BFN, Luis Pedro Fique 119, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: Relaxed rooms & dorms with shared bathrooms in unassuming lodging featuring a kitchen & a bar.
detail_description: Antarctica Hostel is a cozy and sociable lodging located in the heart of Ushuaia's city center. The bright and colorful decor creates a warm atmosphere, and the communal area is perfect for meeting fellow travelers. The hostel offers comfortable rooms with shared bathrooms, complimentary toiletries, and a substantial breakfast. It also features a fully equipped common kitchen for self-catering.
name: Antarctica Hostel
address: IEF, Antártida Argentina 270, V9410IEA Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Torre al Sur is a charming hostel nestled in the heart of Ushuaia, just a stone's throw from Encerrada Bay and conveniently close to Tierra del Fuego National Park. While its exterior may not be the most eye-catching, stepping inside reveals a warm and inviting atmosphere that feels like home. The hostel boasts excellent amenities including free WiFi, cozy common areas for relaxation or games, and self-catering facilities alongside complimentary breakfast to fuel your adventures.
name: Torre al Sur
address: Gdor. Paz 855, V9410 BAQ, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Monseñor Fagnano is a charming hotel nestled in the picturesque town of Ushuaia, Argentina. This delightful establishment offers guests a cozy retreat with stunning views of the surrounding mountains and waterways. The warm ambiance and attentive service create an inviting atmosphere for travelers seeking relaxation after exploring the breathtaking landscapes of Tierra del Fuego.
name: Monseñor Fagnano
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: Straightforward hotel offering old-school, unpretentious rooms, some with water views.
detail_description: The Hostal Malvinas is a simple and old-fashioned hotel in the center of Ushuaia. The rooms have views of the city, are comfortable and clean, and offer free Wi-Fi. The staff is helpful and friendly.
name: Hostal Malvinas
address: Gdor. Deloqui 615, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Patagonia Austral Apartamentos is situated in Ushuaia, just 400 meters from the downtown area and 1 km from Encerrada Bay. The accommodations offer basic but excellent value private apartments with amenities such as TV, towels, and bed linen. While the facilities are basic, they provide everything needed for a comfortable stay. The location is convenient, being close to the center yet away from tourist traffic and closer to the mountains for fresher air.
name: Patagonia Austral Apartamentos
address: Magallanes 1120, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: Warm rooms in a laid-back, rustic B&B offering an airy lounge area & accordion classes.
detail_description: The bed and breakfast Tango B&B is located in the small town of Ushuaia, on the outskirts of the city. It features panoramic views of the Ushuaia Bay and is a 15-minute walk from downtown. Rooms are warm and cozy, with lovely owners and staff. The free Tango show offered at the bed & breakfast can be enjoyed by guests who stay longer than 3 nights.
name: Tango B&B
address: Gdor. Manuel Fernández Valdez 950, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: The Ushuaia City Tour is a great way to explore the city and learn about its history. The tour begins with a visit to the historical La Mission Neighborhood, where the first colonials settled. It's an ideal option for those with limited time or mobility, offering a one-hour sightseeing trip with multilingual audio guides and stops at local recommendations. The tour also includes vouchers for free hot chocolate and discounts on local activities.
name: Ushuaia City Tour
address: Av. Maipú 450, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Cerro Alarkén, home to the Arakur Resort & Spa, is a luxurious retreat nestled within the Cerro Alarken Nature Reserve. The resort offers a romantic atmosphere and stunning views of Tierra del Fuego, with convenient proximity to local attractions. Visitors can explore the reserve's trails, ranging from easy walks through beautiful forests to panoramic vistas of the city and valleys.
name: Cerro Alarkén
address: V9410, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

excerpt: Low-key shopping arcade with a modest mix of cafes, apparel stores & other snug boutiques.
name: Shopping center paseo de compras
address: Av. San Martín 788, V9410BFU Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: The renowned vessel "Saint Christopher" is a stranded ship on the shores of the Beagle Channel, around a century ago. It was positioned there with the purpose of aiding in the rescue of the Monte Cervantes cruise, although this endeavor proved unsuccessful. Nowadays, it has become an iconic sight in Ushuaia and an ideal location for capturing stunning tourist photographs. Adding to its allure would be additional pictures featuring a sign. Unfortunately, there is currently no available information regarding this shipwreck.
name: Saint Christopher
address: Av. Maipú 822, V9410BJR Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Patagonia is a charming destination adorned with vintage antiques and books, creating a cozy atmosphere. Visitors are also delighted by the unique and cheerful bathroom decor.
name: Patagonia
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Cerro Martial, located at the base of the Martial Glacier, is a haven for outdoor enthusiasts. The area offers easy access to hiking trails and ski slopes, making it perfect for those who love adventure. With a few cozy hotels and lodges nearby, visitors can enjoy a comfortable stay while being surrounded by breathtaking natural beauty. Hiking to the top provides stunning views of Ushuaia, but it's recommended to have plenty of free time as the climb can be more challenging than expected.
name: Glacial Martial - Cerro Martial
address: Luis Fernando Martial, Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Tours By Design - Tierra del Fuego Argentina offers a variety of exciting excursions, including the 4x4 lake road adventure. The tour provides breathtaking landscapes and rich historical insights. With knowledgeable guides like Lautaro, visitors can expect an engaging experience filled with interesting facts and stories. Additionally, the trek to Laguna Esmeralda is another highlight, featuring excellent transfer services and expert guidance from professionals like Lucas.
name: Tours By Design - Tierra del Fuego Argentina
address: 136, Agente Manuel Camiña, Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Penguins Flats 5 is a charming accommodation option located in a prime area, offering easy access to the city's main attractions. The property features well-appointed rooms with modern amenities and comfortable furnishings. Guests can enjoy stunning views of the surrounding area from the windows and take advantage of convenient facilities such as a fully equipped kitchen and spacious living areas. With its cozy atmosphere and convenient location, Penguins Flats 5 provides an ideal base for travelers looking to explore the city while enjoying a comfortable stay.
name: Penguins Flats 5
address: Goleta Florencia 2008, V9410BHH Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Bahía Ensenada is a charming bay nestled in the Tierra del Fuego National Park, celebrated for its serene and captivating natural scenery. The area offers an array of picturesque hiking trails, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in the tranquil beauty of this coastal gem.
name: Bahía Ensenada
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Mirador del Beagle is a charming hostel/lodge offering stunning views of Ushuaia and its surroundings. The well-maintained trail provides an excellent vantage point overlooking Ushuaia Bay and the Beagle Channel, making it a must-visit for hikers. Despite occasional foggy weather, visitors can still appreciate the beauty of being in the southernmost city in the world. The low foot traffic on the trail ensures a peaceful experience, although it may be muddy at times.
name: Mirador del Beagle
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Casa de la Mujer in Ushuaia is a multifunctional government building with playgrounds for kids and a mini-park offering a great city view. The rooftop terrace, accessible by two ramps covered in artificial grass, features a metal portrait of Eva Peron. Although the original design aimed to create undulating ramps resembling a maternal womb, it was simplified during construction. Visitors can enjoy outdoor mate sessions and appreciate the well-maintained space suitable for leisurely walks.
name: Casa de la Mujer
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: "Beauty Looks" is a salon known for its exceptional hairdressing services and outstanding customer care. Clients have expressed their satisfaction with the transformation they experience after visiting the salon, often leaving feeling like royalty. The staff's dedication to their work has earned them a reputation for consistently delivering excellent results, making customers feel truly valued and beautiful.
name: Beauty Looks
address: Kuanip 2021, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Historia Fueguina is more than just a typical museum. In addition to its interesting exhibits, visitors can enjoy local specialties at the restaurant located upstairs. The fish stew is especially recommended for its delicious and memorable taste.
name: Historia Fueguina
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Austral, also known as the Carretera Austral, is a breathtaking route in Patagonia that is best experienced at a leisurely pace by driving in your own rental car. The scenic drive offers spectacular views and is perfect for those looking to immerse themselves in the natural beauty of the region.
name: Austral
address: V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: Hom Stay Erica offers a tranquil setting near a beautiful lake, perfect for fishing and hiking. The surrounding hills provide scenic views and various adventure options. Visitors can choose to camp at Lake Escondido or join guided tours for a full day of exploration. Guests praise the comfortable accommodations and excellent service provided by the hosts.
name: Home Stay Erica
address: Juan Facundo Quiroga 1293, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

name: Andes Fueguino
address: Gdor. Deloqui 1536, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: If you're looking for an unforgettable outdoor experience in Ushuaia, look no further than Native Adventure Tours, Rental & Luggage Storage. This company offers a variety of thrilling activities that cater to all adventure seekers. From exhilarating packrafting on the Olivia River to scenic canoeing and trekking excursions led by knowledgeable guides like Juan, Gustavo, and Agustin, every moment is filled with excitement and beauty.
name: -Native Adventure- Tours, Rental & Luggage Storage
address: Gdor. Deloqui 756, V9410 Ushuaia, Tierra del Fuego, Argentina

detail_description: If you're on the lookout for a wholesale supplier that truly stands out, Distribuidora Three Cities is your go-to destination. This unique business prides itself on offering an impressive selection of gourmet products, including a diverse range of supplies and beverages like fine wines. Customers rave about the exceptional quality and variety available, making it a favorite among those who appreciate good taste without breaking the bank. With personalized service and timely deliveries at its core, Distribuidora Three Cities ensures that every interaction feels special.
